<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3759581>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Discorsotheres camposi Ahyong, 2018, juvenile female (cl 3.8 mm, cw 3.8 mm), Deverd Pass, New Caledonia, MNHN IU-2019-5221: A, dorsal; B, in host, Spondylus varius Sowerby, 1827. Viridotheres asaphis sp. nov., ovigerous female paratype, cl 6.1 mm, cw 7.2 mm, Ohland Bay, near Paagoumene, New Caledonia, MNHN IU-2019-5158: C, dorsal; D, in host, Asaphis violascens (Forskål, 1775)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3759581/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3759583>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Viridotheres asaphis sp. nov., female holotype, cl 6.1 mm, cw 7.2 mm, Palm Island, Queensland, Australia, AM P104025.A, dorsal habitus; B, right maxilliped 3; C, left cheliped fingers, distal mesial view; D, right chela; E, anterior cephalothorax; F, anterior thoracic sternum (setae omitted); F; G–J, right pereopods 2–5; K, left pereopod 3, dactylus-propodus-carpus; L, abdominal somites (II–VI) and telson (VII). Scale: A, L = 2.0 mm; B, C = 0.5 mm; D–K = 1.0 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3759583/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

